# .cursorrules — Event-Driven Status Tracker v2.1
# These rules are IMMUTABLE for this project.
# If any generation violates these rules, flag the violation before proceeding.

## Language & Runtime
- Python 3.11+ exclusively — use Python 3.11+ syntax features freely
- Use `async def` for ALL FastAPI route handlers and dependency functions
- Use `def` (sync) ONLY for pure, stateless business logic (processor.py)
- Type hints are MANDATORY on every function signature — no untyped parameters ever

## Framework Stack — No Substitutions Permitted
- Web framework: FastAPI only (no Flask, no Django, no Starlette direct)
- ASGI server: Uvicorn only (no gunicorn, no hypercorn)
- Validation: Pydantic v2 BaseModel only (ConfigDict, not class Config)
- Testing: pytest + FastAPI TestClient only
- HTTP client (if needed): httpx only

## Startup and Environment
- ALWAYS call load_dotenv() as the FIRST executable statement in main.py,
  before ANY os.environ.get() calls or logging.basicConfig() calls.
  Without this, the .env file is entirely ignored by the process.
- LOG_LEVEL MUST be read from os.environ, not hardcoded.
- PRODUCTION_MODE MUST be read from os.environ.

## Security Rules — Absolute, No Exceptions
- Content-Type: application/json MUST be validated BEFORE HMAC computation.
  Return HTTP 415 for non-JSON Content-Type — do NOT fall through to 422.
- HMAC-SHA256 signature verification on EVERY POST /webhook request.
- ALWAYS use hmac.compare_digest() — NEVER == or != for signature comparison.
- ALWAYS extract raw request body bytes BEFORE any JSON parsing for HMAC.
- WEBHOOK_SECRET loaded from os.environ ONLY — never hardcoded in source.
- Return HTTP 401 immediately and unconditionally on ANY signature failure.
- Return HTTP 415 immediately on Content-Type mismatch.
- NEVER log the actual secret value, even partially.

## Body Size Protection
- BodySizeLimitMiddleware MUST be registered on the FastAPI app.
- MAX_BODY_BYTES = 1_048_576 (1MB). Atlassian payloads are always < 50KB.
- Middleware checks Content-Length header. Returns HTTP 413 if exceeded.
- This must fire BEFORE the HMAC dependency runs.

## Async Rules — Event Loop Protection
- NEVER call blocking I/O directly in async route handlers.
- ALL post-validation processing MUST go through FastAPI BackgroundTasks.
- Route handlers MUST return HTTP 202 BEFORE the background task executes.
- NEVER use asyncio.sleep() or time.sleep() in route handlers.

## Background Task Tracking
- ALWAYS wrap process_status_update() in _tracked_process_status_update().
- _tracked_process_status_update() maintains _active_tasks_count via threading.Lock.
- threading.Lock MUST be used — NOT asyncio.Lock — because background tasks
  run in a thread pool executor, not the async event loop.
- Lifespan shutdown polls _active_tasks_count for up to 10 seconds.

## Idempotency
- processor.py MUST check component_update.id and incident.id against
  _seen_event_ids (thread-safe set with threading.Lock) before processing.
- Cache is bounded at _DEDUP_CACHE_MAX = 500 entries (FIFO eviction).
- If id is None (older Atlassian payload), skip dedup and process unconditionally.
- Both requests in a duplicate pair MUST return HTTP 202 — dedup is transparent
  at the HTTP layer. Only console output is suppressed for duplicates.

## Validation Rules
- ALL incoming JSON validated through Pydantic models before any processing.
- Optional fields: use Optional[str] = None — never assume field presence.
- Malformed payloads: HTTP 422 returned automatically by Pydantic.
- Unknown fields: model_config = ConfigDict(extra='ignore') on ALL models.

## MONITORED_KEYWORDS (Runtime-Configurable Filter)
- MONITORED_PRODUCTS in processor.py MUST be loaded from the MONITORED_KEYWORDS
  environment variable at module import time.
- If MONITORED_KEYWORDS is absent or empty, use the hardcoded default list.
- Changing the filter requires only an env var update and restart — no code change.
- Non-matching components: silently drop in processor, always return HTTP 202.

## Imports — Explicit and Complete
- ALWAYS import Optional from typing when used in type annotations.
- ALWAYS import ConfigDict from pydantic when using model_config.
- No wildcard imports (from module import *).
- No circular imports.

## Logging — Production Standard
- ALWAYS use Python standard logging module — never bare print() statements.
- Log format: "%(message)s" at INFO level (message only, no extra prefixes).
- ERROR level for security rejections.
- DEBUG level for filtered-but-valid events and dedup discards.

## Error Handling
- FastAPI HTTPException with explicit status_code is the ONLY error mechanism.
- Never swallow exceptions silently — log.error() at minimum before any exit path.
- Fail-fast: validate at the boundary (the HTTP handler), never inside logic.

## Testing Standards
- EVERY route needs: happy-path, invalid-signature, missing-signature, bad content-type.
- Use monkeypatch.setenv() for environment variable injection — never os.environ mutation.
- Use generate_valid_signature() helper for all test payload signing.
- Assert BOTH status_code AND response body content in every test.
- Test helper MUST use json.dumps(payload, separators=(',', ':')) to match httpx encoding.
- Dedup tests MUST reset _seen_event_ids and _seen_event_ids_order before execution.

## Code Style
- Max line length: 100 characters.
- Docstrings on every function and class.
- No unused imports — remove them.
- Use f-strings for string formatting, not .format() or %.

## Git Discipline
- Commit after every atomic step that passes its tests.
- NEVER commit .env files (ensured by .gitignore).
- Tag releases: v1.0.0, v1.1.0, etc.
